This is your average GNOME desktop showing you your favorite applications on the Dash as well as your most-used applications. Can you see the problem?

You have a place where you put your favorite (i.e. most-used, otherwise why would you consider them your favorites?) applications that is small and limited compared to yet another place where you find the same icons; except that it can take more icons, doesn't get awkwardly resized and is dynamic, meaning that you don't need to do anything if you don't use an application as much as you used to and it'll disspear.
